main event: A witness reported seeing a glowing, self-illuminating, solid circular object with fuzzy edges in the sky near Bellefontaine, Ohio on May 20, 1968.
interesting points: The object was observed while the witness was driving and appeared to move from east to south.
The witness described the object as being about the size of a quarter, making no precise 90-degree turns, and making a humming sound.
The witness initially said the sky was clear, but later said a small aircraft was also in the area, which first drew their attention to the object.
The witness had reported a similar sighting of a black, cigar-shaped object that turned bluish-white and disappeared in April 1968.
The investigating officer did not feel the report was reliable.
sighted object: a glowing, self-illuminating, solid circular object with fuzzy edges
